    "actor_description": "The next moment has weight. My attention keeps snapping forward as if it can catch what's coming before it arrives. I feel it in my body: a held breath, fingertips wanting to move, muscles lightly pre-tensed—ready without being afraid. I keep checking small cues, rehearsing the first action like a reflex test. It's not panic. It's timing. Like standing a half-step from a starting line, waiting for the signal that makes the whole world go.",
    "description_text": "{actor} goes still in a way that isn't restful—weight subtly forward, eyes tracking, attention snagging on every small change. Their hands flex once and settle. Breath runs a little high, controlled. They look prepared, not worried: someone measuring distance and seconds, waiting for the exact moment to move.",
